<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hi again Toodle, thanks for your vote of confidence.<P>Elasto, actually, having buffs only in the second bank would be enough to appease the people here who support the idea of having more slots, since it's usually the buffs that you have to constantly swap in and out because you have your battle-intensive spells filling all your slots. It would also appease people who are deluding themselves with the idea that choosing which spells to rack somehow equates to the work of a genius. If extra spell slots were implemented in this way I would not complain.<P>Arlina, once again you surpass yourself in your attempts to make your ignorance clear to all posting here...<P>Your point: "I even gave you a chance to prove your point about spell gems which you (unsurprisingly) dodged"<P>I didn't take you up on your juvenile offer because it has literally nothing to do with what is being discussed here. The point is we do NOT want to swap spells in and out during battle. We already know which spells we need, but we don't have the facility to use them without tedious messing about with spell slots. Quandary pointed this out to you in a much better way than I can, and you missed his point completely too. You really need to wake up.<P>Another gem from Arlina: "After pointing out that, at least for jewelcrafting, the time spent purchasing was very small compared to the time spent combining and selling, you've ceased to attempt to support this point."<P>How do you fail to understand that if the stacking problem was not a 'flaw' Verant would never have fixed it? How do you fail to understand that taking two years to fix such a fundamental problem is wholly unacceptable? How do you fail to understand that counting out items slowly is a) time-consuming b) boring and c) bad game design?<P>As for your point about doing a quest to get lenses just because you found it interesting, lol, if you found that interesting I can see how Verant have got away with so much for so long with people like you around.<P>I think Toodle is right. Some of the people posting here work for VI. Reading your posts, we could very easily be forgiven for thinking you are one of them.
