<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
You do JC so you are the resident tradeskill expert? Say I want to do some minor mid to low level smithing. Now I usually will buy around 6-8 stacks of ore, then 3-4 stacks of water.(not doing alot today   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">) Then combine in a forge. So, 160 clicks for ore, and 80 for water. Now when I go to put it in the forge (not long ago) I had to slide the little bar to 1, put it in the forge. Slide the bar to 1, put in the forge, and slide the bar to 1.. put in the forge. Hit combine. Crap, failed. noooo metal bits are trivial. Why am I still making them? Because in order to advance my skill, i need to make studs, or skewers. The mid level stuff requires the metal bits. Studs for example take 3 metal bits, and a flask of water (and a file, but that isn't consumed). It produces 2 studs (when you succeed). So metal bits are 2 pieces of ore and 1 water. 2 stacks of ore and a stack of water equal ONE stack of bits if you never fail (not likely   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">). But for arguements sake...60 clicks to buy the materials to make 1 stack of metal bits. so, 180 clicks for the materials (3 stacks of metal bits) and another 20 for a stack of water. That'll make 2 stacks of studs in a perfect world. So 200 clicks to make some studs.. which you'll burn up in no time doing studded leather. Btw, that only accounts for the buying of the components. Not sliding the bar over, putting into forge, stacking, etc. So as you can see. It WAS a huge problem to tradespeople. Sorry for the rambling, but JC isn't the best skill to be representing the flaw in the system.<P>Also, the 'strategy of spells' is a lame strategy that people are just grasping to find. If you wanted strategy, have location based damage, elevation based percentages, etc. The idea that having to choose which of your 'preset' spells to drop in order to buff is weak. In a good pull situation, you won't have to be worried about what you drop, usually whichever mems the fastest to reduce the time your group has to wait before pulling again. The strategy comes really from how your group acts in the fight. Every enchanter will have some mez spell memmed. Damn. we have another ****ing Patten on our hands. What a brilliant strategist! The actual strategy comes into the groups ability to assist the main tank, stay away from mezzed mobs, etc. Even that is lame since the strategy is basically the same no matter what. It's not like, let's rush them from the top of the hill from behind now that the monk has distracted their attention. It's more like... you idiot. I just mezzed that. ahh zone zone zone Train to zone. The magic zone which makes all our troubles disappear ;P.<BR>You have gotten better at ranting (81).<P>--------------------<P>Bertox Server<BR>-------------<BR>21 Bard - Alluen &ltNew Dawn&gt<BR>13 Enchanter - Epicurius &ltLegends of Light&gt<BR>10 Rogue - Fleck
