Quote from Toodle<P>"Verant addressed this issue and said it was too "hard" to add extra slots, both from a programming angle, and that of the screen design. The other justifications are just that and came later."<P>Quote from Navigator<P>"Game mechanics? These are what the coders decide they want them to be. I'm a 20 year coder so don't try blowing smoke up my kilt on this one. This a no-brainer unless you have coded yourself into box somehow, and if that's the case, then now would be a good time to start the rewrite."<P>Do you have any clue what you are talking about Navigator.  I am a Software Developer and you obviously have no idea what your talking about.  If this change was easy Verant has stated they would consider doing it.  If it isn't easy for an entire team of coders, why act like it is so easy.  It comes down to priorities and Verant has decided the amount of work doesn't warrant the feature.<P>Let's say Verant decides to update this feature.  Well you have to change the interface to have more slots.  Where will you put these slots.  Will you add more key features for them.  What about the different resolutions.  Coding is only one part of Software Development.  In Software Development you have a limited amount of coding resources(the programmers) and usually a larger amount of work than they can all do.  So you have to prioritize the work.  If you have a feature that takes 400 programming hours(10 average programmers one week) are you going to work on it when you have other issues more critical.  The bugs, expansions(get more money), more critical features are on the plate.  In fact the amount of stuff on the plate is so large that spell slots aren't even on the plate.<P>Now whether Verant could afford to hire more resources to get us more features is their business.  I know I sure would like to see some more.  In all fairness though I think they have beefed their team up a little now that they realize this game is ongoing.
