<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Arlina's point (As far as I can make out) is that having eight slots limits the things a caster can do. A caster with many spells (Ex. Enchanter) must choose between stuns, mez, charm, defense, root, short duration melee buffs, whatever. This caster cannot do all of these things at once, and the strategy is deciding which ones to use in a given amount of time, maybe sacrificing root for stun or whatnot. Though it seems your defeating your class in limiting your power as an enchanter, you have a point. There is strategy in deciding whether to keep one spell available at the cost of another.<P>  HOWEVER! There is the other side of the coin. Shamans, clerics, druids, have lots of nifty spells. Unfortunately, a lot of these nifty spells are called "buffs". Swapping spells so one can buff is tedious and not strategy in any way shape or form.<P>  Keeping the second spell bank reserved for buffs would be a fine compromise. This wouldn't infringe on the strategy of selecting spells at all, IMHO.<P>My opinion:  <P>Personally, however, I'd really like for my local enchanter or cleric to be able to more of her skills. It'd have saved my rear a bit more if they'd been able to, in the past. I'd LOVE to see an increase of slots as we level up, in fact one additional one every spell rank (1, 4, 8, 12) would be great. Perhaps start with 6, end with 12 or 16. This would make sense, too. Besides, everyone knows casters are unbalanced vs. melee, and this change would primarily enhance enchanter/cleric abilities, and save druids, shamans, and clerics a lot of trouble. Too bad for the rest of the INT casters.. but that's another thread that belongs in wizards' rants forums. (I have a wizard and I'll fill your ear with it, but I'm getting off-topic.)<P>  It seems everyone is ignoring everyone else and making personal attacks. *sigh* Having a "discussion" in this way doesn't do much except waste our time.<P>*remaining anonymous, as it's easier to make a point if people aren't already biased against your name because of what you've said earlier*
