<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Did nobody listen to the explaination of why they missed it?  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>For debugging purposes pretty much all game designers have additional code to run stuff in a different mode than normal. Why do you think video games have cheat codes? They were first introduced to facilitate debugging, NOT because of the demand to have a god mode.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> Anyways, the debug environment had some variable different (when it shouldn't have been different) than the live environment, and alchemy worked in their debug environment.<P>Arlina
